        <scopecontent>
            <p>
The Fred Crawford Papers consists of the research material gathered by Central Michigan University Professor Fred Crawford from 1991 to 1998 for a biography on Lowell Thomas. Most of the material within the collection appears to have been maintained in an orderly fashion by Fred Crawford. The lone exception to this is Series 2 which may have been the material Crawford was currently working on as well as assorted on-hand and reference material. While the order within most of the file series was not maintained during the transport to Marist College, the original order was recreated during processing based on the detail of Crawford’s original folder descriptions. These descriptions were maintained when possible with alterations made only for consistency and completion. Misfiles that appeared to be organic were maintained to preserve as much of Crawford’s original and unique order as possible.
</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <userestrict>
            <p>
The items in folders one through ten have no restrictions. All items in folder Eleven: Research Materials and Secondary Sources, have copyrights retained by the original authors or their descendants, as stipulated by United States copyright law http://www.loc.gov/copyright/title17/.
</p>
